'''Buttoned Down Disco''' is a large and long-running [[London]] nightclub playing [[Independent_music|indie]] and [[Electro_(music)|electro]] founded by Christian Laing and Rachel Laing, with Christian as the resident DJ.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buttoneddowndisco.com/about|title=What is Buttoned Down Disco about? - Buttoned Down Disco - London nightclub playing pop, indie, punk, electro, funk and disco at KOKO in Camden|author=|date=|website=www.ButtonedDownDisco.com|access-date=8 September 2017}}</ref>

The first night was in October 2002. The location of the club was revealed after an electronic invitation was requested. A pioneering concept<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2007/jan/06/freestuff.guardianspecial419|title=Party on at Paddington|first1=Kate|last1=Abbott|first2=Holly|last2=Bentley|date=6 January 2007|publisher=|accessdate=8 September 2017|via=The Guardian}}</ref> at the time. In 2006, Buttoned Down Disco became a resident at [[KOKO (music venue)|KOKO]] and continues there to this day<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buttoneddowndisco.com/press/telegraph-londons-best-nightlife|title=The Telegraph: London's best nightlife - Buttoned Down Disco - London nightclub playing pop, indie, punk, electro, funk and disco at KOKO in Camden|website=www.ButtonedDownDisco.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buttoneddowndisco.com/press/guardian-preview|title=The Guardian: Preview - Buttoned Down Disco - London nightclub playing pop, indie, punk, electro, funk and disco at KOKO in Camden|website=www.ButtonedDownDisco.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buttoneddowndisco.com/press/independent-ten-best-club-nights|title=The Independent: Ten best club nights - Buttoned Down Disco - London nightclub playing pop, indie, punk, electro, funk and disco at KOKO in Camden|website=www.buttoneddowndisco.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buttoneddowndisco.com/press/times-top-five-clubs-0|title=The Times: Top Five Clubs - Buttoned Down Disco - London nightclub playing pop, indie, punk, electro, funk and disco at KOKO in Camden|author=|date=|website=www.ButtonedDownDisco.com|access-date=8 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buttoneddowndisco.com/press/timeout-review|title=TimeOut: Review - Buttoned Down Disco - London nightclub playing pop, indie, punk, electro, funk and disco at KOKO in Camden|website=www.ButtonedDownDisco.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buttoneddowndisco.com/press/timeout-londons-best-indie-nights|title=TimeOut: London's best indie nights - Buttoned Down Disco - London nightclub playing pop, indie, punk, electro, funk and disco at KOKO in Camden|website=www.ButtonedDownDisco.com}}</ref>. Buttoned Down Disco has also taken place in major festivals including [[Glastonbury_Festival|Glastonbury]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glastonburyfestivals.co.uk/areas/williams-green/|title=Glastonbury Festival - William’s Green|first=Pretty Good|last=Digital|website=Glastonbury Festival - 21st-25th June, 2017}}</ref>, [[Lovebox_Festival|Lovebox]], [[Reading_and_Leeds_Festivals|Reading]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfestival.com/line-up/artist/buttoned-down-disco|title=Buttoned Down Disco|first=|last=admin|date=7 June 2017|publisher=}}</ref> and [[Latitude_Festival|Latitude]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latitudefestival.com/line-up/artist/buttoned-down-disco|title=Buttoned Down Disco|first=|last=admin|date=10 May 2017|publisher=}}</ref>. 

Buttoned Down Disco took its name from the third track from [[Cornershop (band)|Cornershop]]'s disco inspired album ''Disco and the Halfway to Discontent'' as part of their side-project, Clinton. The club then influenced the song "M.R.S.T." by The Electric Riot where "Buttoned Down Discos" were mentioned in the lyrics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musixmatch.com/lyrics/The-Electric-Riot/M-R-S-T|title=The Electric Riot - M.R.S.T Lyrics - Musixmatch|author=|date=|website=musiXmatch|access-date=8 September 2017}}</ref>

