{{Infobox games | name = FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1939 | logo = FIS Nordic WSC 1939 program cover.jpg | size = 200px | caption = Program cover for the FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1939. {{pl icon}} | host city = [[Zakopane]] | country = Poland | motto = | nations participating = | teams participating = | debuting countries = | athletes participating = | events = 5 | opening ceremony = {{Start date|1939|2|11|df=y}} | closing ceremony = {{End date|1939|2|19|df=y}} | officially opened by = | athlete's oath = | judge's oath = | torch lighter = | stadium = | length = | indprize = | tmprize = | website = | previous = [[FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1938|1938]] | next = [[FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1941|1941]] }} The '''FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1939''' took place February 11–19, 1939 in [[Zakopane]], [[Poland]]. This was the Polish city's second time hosting the championships after having done so in [[FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 1929|1929]]. It also marked the last time the event officially took place before [[World War II]] and the last time that these championships would be held on an annual basis (combined with the [[Winter Olympics]]) which they had been done since 1924.
