[[File:Niderviller-foire de Lyon 1948.jpg|thumb|Booth of the [[Niderviller pottery|Niderviller group]] at the Lyon fair, 1948]] The '''Fair of Lyon''' ('''{{lang-fr|Foire de Lyon}}'''; or '''''{{lang|fr|Foire internationale de Lyon}}''''') is a [[trade fair]], traditionally held in March in [[Lyon]], France. Begun as an initiative by Lyon mayor [[Édouard Herriot]] in 1916, the fair has been held in the [[Eurexpo]] convention center in [[Chassieu]] since 1985.
== History ==
[[File:Lyon - Place des Terreaux.jpg|thumb|Engraving of [[Place des Terreaux]] decorated to celebrate the Fair of Lyon, by {{Interlanguage link multi|Charles Pinet|fr}}]]
The creation of the Fair of Lyon began in 1916 through an initiative by then mayor [[Édouard Herriot]]. He decided to build a vast "Palace" to accommodate the commercial stalls that were crowding the quays and streets, and impeding traffic flow in the area. The Fair Palace was built from 1918 to 1938 on land located between the [[Rhône]] and [[Parc de la Tête d'Or]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Charles|last=Delfante|title=Cent Ans d'Urbanisme à Lyon|edition=LUGD|pp=164-165|year=1994|isbn=978-2841470044|language=fr}}</ref> Subsequent construction did not adhere to the original plan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popsu.archi.fr/sites/default/files/nodes/document/667/files/lyon-cite-internationale.pdf|title=La Cité Internationale|website=Plate-Forme D'Observation Des Projets et Stratégies Urbaines|date=June 2006|access-date=13 January 2016|language=fr}}</ref> The buildings of the Fair Palace were ultimately destroyed to make room for the [[Cité Internationale]], leaving only the main façade of the central pavilion, now integrated into the [[Musée d'art contemporain de Lyon]]. In 1985 the fair was moved to the [[Eurexpo]] convention center in the commune of [[Chassieu]], east of the [[Metropolis of Lyon]].
== Themes ==
Each edition of the fair, starting from 2006, is devoted to a particular theme.
* 2006{{sndash}}The People of Tibet, with [[Maurice Herzog]] as sponsor * 2007{{sndash}}Indonesia * 2008{{sndash}}India * 2009{{sndash}}Cinema, with [[Clovis Cornillac]] as sponsor * 2010{{sndash}}[[Japanese culture]] * 2011{{sndash}}[[Outer space]] and [[science fiction]] * 2012{{sndash}}Native Americans, with sponsor Harlyn Geronimo, great grandson of [[Geronimo]] * 2013{{sndash}}New York&nbsp;– New York! Exposition on New York City, with [[Douglas Kennedy (writer)|Douglas Kennedy]] as sponsor * 2014{{sndash}}Rock Story, an exposition on the history of [[Rock music|rock]], with [[Philippe Manœuvre]] as artistic advisor and sponsor * 2015{{sndash}}{{lang|fr|Les objets connectés}} (Connected Objects) * 2016{{sndash}}{{lang|fr|La foire de Lyon fête ses 100 ans !}} (The Fair of Lyon Celebrates 100 Years!) * 2017{{sndash}}Viva Cuba
