{{Infobox recurring event | name= FestivalandCo | logo= | image= Shakespeare & Co Books, Paris April 2011.jpg | caption= [[Shakespeare and Company (bookshop)|Shakespeare and Company]], Paris, 2011. | location= [[Paris, France]] | years_active= | founded= | dates= | genre= [[Literary festival]] | attendance= | patron= | website= {{url|festivalandco.com}} }}
'''''FestivalandCo''''' is a [[literary festival]] held in [[Paris, France]] at the [[Shakespeare and Company (bookstore)|Shakespeare and Company]] bookstore.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/22/arts/22iht-bookfest.html The New York Times]</ref><ref>[http://www.english.rfi.fr/culture/20100620-storytelling-politics-and-sex-shakespeare-and-company-festival English.rfi.fr]</ref><ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/historic-paris-bookstore-to-relaunch-literary-magazine-1990287.html Independent.co.uk]</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Turning the page at Shakespeare and Company|work=The Telegraph | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/expat/expatlife/9643855/Turning-the-page-at-Shakespeare-and-Company.html |author=Leah Hyslop|date=9 Nov 2012|accessdate = 2014-10-14 }}</ref>
[[Sylvia Beach Whitman]]<ref>[http://www.theparistimes.com/content/Inheriting+Tradition The Paris Times]</ref> founded the festival which has hosted such writers as [[Paul Auster]], [[Siri Hustvedt]], [[Jeanette Winterson]], [[David Hare (playwright)|David Hare]], [[Jung Chang]] and [[Marjane Satrapi]].<ref>[http://www.festivalandco.com Festivalandco.com]</ref><ref>[http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/books/article7125241.ece Timesonline.co.uk]</ref>
