{{nofootnotes|date=June 2010}} {{refimprove|date=June 2010}}
'''June Events''' are alternatives to [[May Ball]]s held by some [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] colleges.
The necessarily high price of [[May Ball]] tickets motivates some colleges to host Events instead.{{fact|date=June 2010}} These evenings, tending to be shorter in duration and of a much lower key, are more affordable but constrained by a much lower budget.
==Alternation== Some colleges chose to alternate between a May Ball and a June Event each year.{{fact|date=June 2010}} [[Emmanuel College, Cambridge|Emmanuel College]]'s May Ball is held in May Week every other year, with alternate years featuring an Event on [[Suicide Sunday]].{{fact|date=June 2010}}
In 2006, members of the College voted in favour of restoring [[Pembroke College, Cambridge|Pembroke College]]'s lost tradition of hosting a May Ball for 2007.{{fact|date=June 2010}} In 2008 they will hold another June Event.
== External links == * [http://www.thjuneevent.co.uk/ Trinity Hall June Event] * [http://www.emmaevent.co.uk Emmanuel June Event] * [http://www.kingsaffair.com/ King's Affair] * [http://www.pembrokejuneevent.co.uk/ Pembroke June Event] * [http://www.wolfsonjuneevent.co.uk Wolfson June Event]
