[[Image:newyear07.jpg|right|200px|thumb|The Peach Drop's tower at its former location in Underground Atlanta.]]

The '''Peach Drop''' is an annual [[New Year's Eve]] [[List of objects dropped on New Year's Eve|drop]] event held in [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]. From 1989 through 2017, the event was held at [[Underground Atlanta]], but has since been held at [[Woodruff Park]]. The drop's use of a peach symbolizes Georgia's identity as the "Peach State".

As Underground Atlanta was sold to a private developer, the Drop was held there for the last time for 2016-17. Since 2018, the drop has occurred from the [[Flatiron Building (Atlanta)|Flatiron Building]], with festivities at [[Woodruff Park]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ajc.com/news/crime--law/atlanta-police-ramp-security-plans-for-new-peach-drop-location/2kzTML6beejWaANAcJyAAL/|title=Atlanta police ramp up security plans for new Peach Drop location|last=Stevens|first=Alexis|website=Atlanta Journal-Constitution|access-date=2017-12-29}}</ref>

